The provided solution should work on modern mobile devices, but there are some caveats:

1. Mobile browser support for WebRTC, getUserMedia, and related APIs may vary. Most modern browsers on Android devices (Chrome, Firefox, etc.) should have good support, but iOS devices may have limitations, especially on browsers other than Safari.
2. Mobile devices have limited processing power compared to desktop computers, so performance may not be as smooth, especially when sending and processing audio streams.
3. Mobile devices usually have data usage limits, so sending audio streams to Google Cloud for transcription could consume a significant amount of data. Be mindful of this when designing your application.

